name: UInterchangeBaseNode
doc:
This struct is used to store and retrieve key-value attributes. The attributes are stored in a generic FAttributeStorage that serializes the values in a TArray64<uint8>.
See UE::Interchange::EAttributeTypes to know the supported template types.
This is an abstract class. This is the base class of the interchange node graph format; all classes in this format should derive from this class.

methods.name: AddBooleanAttribute
methods.doc: Add a Boolean attribute to this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist or if it cannot be added.

methods.name: AddDoubleAttribute
methods.doc: Add a double attribute to this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist or if it cannot be added.

methods.name: AddFloatAttribute
methods.doc: Add a float attribute to this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist or if it cannot be added.

methods.name: AddGuidAttribute
methods.doc: Add a GUID attribute to this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist or if it cannot be added.

methods.name: AddInt32Attribute
methods.doc: Add a int32 attribute to this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist or if it cannot be added.

methods.name: AddLinearColorAttribute
methods.doc: Add an FLinearColor attribute to this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist or if it cannot be added.

methods.name: AddStringAttribute
methods.doc: Add a string attribute to this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist or if it cannot be added.

methods.name: AddTargetNodeUid
methods.doc: Add an asset node UID relating to this object.

methods.name: AddVector2Attribute
methods.doc: Add a Vector2 attribute to this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist or if it cannot be added.

methods.name: GetAssetName
methods.doc:
Optional. Any node that can import or export an asset should set the desired name for the asset.
If the attribute was never set, returns GetDisplayLabel().

methods.name: GetBooleanAttribute
methods.doc: Get a Boolean attribute from this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist.

methods.name: GetDisplayLabel
methods.doc: Return the display label.

methods.name: GetDoubleAttribute
methods.doc: Get a double attribute from this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist.

methods.name: GetFloatAttribute
methods.doc: Get a float attribute from this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist.

methods.name: GetGuidAttribute
methods.doc: Get a GUID attribute from this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist.

methods.name: GetInt32Attribute
methods.doc: Get a int32 attribute from this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist.

methods.name: GetLinearColorAttribute
methods.doc: Get an FLinearColor attribute from this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist.

methods.name: GetNodeContainerType
methods.doc: Return the node container type that defines the purpose of the node (factory node, translated scene node, or translated asset node).

methods.name: GetParentUid
methods.doc: Return the parent unique ID. If the attribute does not exist, returns InvalidNodeUid().

methods.name: GetStringAttribute
methods.doc: Get a string attribute from this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist.

methods.name: GetTargetNodeCount
methods.doc: Get the number of target assets relating to this object.

methods.name: GetTargetNodeUids
methods.doc: Get the target assets relating to this object.

methods.name: GetUniqueID
methods.doc: Return the unique ID passed in the constructor.

methods.name: GetVector2Attribute
methods.doc: Get a Vector2 attribute from this node. Returns false if the attribute does not exist.

methods.name: InitializeNode
IsEnabled
methods.doc:
If true, the node is imported or exported. If false, it is discarded.
Returns false if the node was disabled. Returns true if the attribute is not there or if it was enabled.

methods.name: RemoveAttribute
methods.doc: Remove the specified attribute from this node. Returns false if it could not be removed. If the attribute does not exist, returns true.

methods.name: RemoveTargetNodeUid
methods.doc: Remove an asset node UID relating to this object.

methods.name: SetAssetName
methods.doc: Set the name for the imported asset this node represents. The asset factory will call GetAssetName().

methods.name: SetDisplayLabel
methods.doc: Change the display label.

methods.name: SetEnabled
